Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
The winter season in our hometown is very beautiful. Although many trees on longer have leaves on them, there are still many trees keep green. There are lots of pine trees and bamboo in my hometown, alive even in winter. although it does not snow much, it is amazingly beautiful when it snows. The montains and trees are covered with white snow, which looks like a picture of wonderland.